### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

Our beloved NG600 (```Writing to signals is not allowed in a `computed` or an `effect` by default. Use `allowSignalWrites` in the `CreateEffectOptions` to enable this inside effects.``` ) is an error that arrises frequently atm due to people playing a lot with signals. 

From the errors I have been seeing, it seems that the error message is a bit misliding. The error occurs when the is no obvious effect in play. 

For example here, a synchronous tap triggered from the template. 
```
@Component({
  selector: 'my-app',
  template: `Current Count: {{ counter$|async }}`,
})
export class AppComponent {
  private dummy = signal(0);

  private counterSubject = new BehaviorSubject(0);
  counter$ = this.counterSubject.pipe(tap(() => this.dummy.set(1)));
}
```

Edit: Pawel already mentionned [in this comment](https://github.com/angular/angular/issues/49967#issuecomment-1519627030), the reason of why it happens here and that the message does need improvement.

