### Description

Hi, after upgrade from 15.1.0 to 16.0.2 my app is not staring anymore. I'm using monorepo approach with nx.

I noticed that the problem is related to the code generated by angular.
For example, when I have a service like below:

```
@Injectable()
export class TestService extends BaseService {

	public readonly renderer2: Renderer2 = this.getRenderer();

	constructor(private readonly rendererFactory2: RendererFactory2) {
		super();
	}

	getRenderer(): Renderer2 {
		return this.rendererFactory2.createRenderer(null, null);
	}

}
```

The result code in Angular 15 looks like:

```
class TestService extends _bp_util__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_0__.BaseService {
  constructor(rendererFactory2) {
    super();
    this.rendererFactory2 = rendererFactory2;
    this.renderer2 = this.getRenderer();
  }
  getRenderer() {
    return this.rendererFactory2.createRenderer(null, null);
  }
}
```

and After upgrade to Angular 16:

```
 class TestService extends _bp_util__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_1__.BaseService {
  constructor(rendererFactory2) {
    super();
    (0,_app_path_node_modules_angular_devkit_build_angular_node_modules_babel_runtime_helpers_esm_defineProperty_js__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_0__["default"])(this, "rendererFactory2", void 0);
    (0,_app_path_node_modules_angular_devkit_build_angular_node_modules_babel_runtime_helpers_esm_defineProperty_js__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_0__["default"])(this, "renderer2", this.getRenderer());
    this.rendererFactory2 = rendererFactory2;
  }
  getRenderer() {
    return this.rendererFactory2.createRenderer(null, null);
  }
}
```

In Angular 16 to create field `renderer2` code is trying to access `rendererFactory2` that has not been assigned yet, and it throws an error.  

